# Keep the Docker build context small and deterministic. The image only needs
# site/ (the Rust crate) and the built DuckDB store from data/.

# ─── Build artifacts / VCS / tooling not needed to build the image ───
**/target
.git
.github
.claude
skills
docs
pipeline
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv
*.md

# ─── data/: ship ONLY the built store (+ optional LM dictionary CSV) ──
# This drops the multi-GB raw HuggingFace dataset directories and any WAL
# sidecar, which would otherwise bloat the build context and the image.
data/*
!data/subtext.duckdb
!data/*.csv
